  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. Operating envelope is explicitly bounded: axial compressive load 0–2400 N, bending moment 0–18 N·m, screw diameter 7.5 mm ± 0.05 mm, construct length 100–110 mm, cortical bone surrogate density 1.6–1.9 g/cm³. Validation dataset covers this envelope densely (N=11 constructs, two labs).",
